1. Download the lite distro of Raspbian.
2. Write it to the SD card with balenaEtcher.
3. Still on your PC, put the files from the "pi_boot" folder onto the boot partition of the Pi's SD card.
4. Complete the WLAN information in the "wpa_supplicant.conf" file.
5. Put the card in the Pi and boot it up. Now it will hopefully connect to your Wifi.
6. Find the IP address by using Fing on android
7. Connect by ssh on WSL.
8. Log in using the default credentials (pi raspberry)
sudo raspi-config to configure to youre liking.
sudo apt-get install python3-pip
pip3 --version

add audio and camera module drivers

check to make sure camera and audio hardware functions